Description: Fragment of flattened handle from a Thasian pottery transport amphora. Clay medium micaceous orange brown. Rectangular stamp at top of handle with Greek inscription and thymiaterion and perhaps axe as symbols.
Curator's comments: Garlan, Y., Les timbres amphoriques de Thasos. 1, Timbres protothasiens et thasiens anciens (Paris 1999) no. 662. He notes two such handles in the Museum from Naukratis, probably in error.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0008)
